 from asymptotic giant branch stars or magneto-rotational\ninstabilities in core-collapse supernovae provide poor fits to the\nobservations. We also report one Phoenix stream star to be a lithium-rich giant\n($A(\\mathrm{Li}) = 3.1 \\pm 0.1$). At $[\\mathrm{Fe/H}] = -2.93$ it is among the\nmost metal-poor lithium-rich giants known.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Sep 2021 22:09:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-17"}
